name: Twin Peaks
overview: The body of Laura Palmer is washed up on a beach near the small Washington state town of Twin Peaks. FBI Special Agent Dale Cooper is called in to investigate her strange demise only to uncover a web of mystery that ultimately leads him deep into the heart of the surrounding woodland and his very own soul.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: It turns out Twin Peaks is not like other towns, and soon FBI Agent Cooper becomes enmeshed with its quirky and mysterious residents.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: The town's dark side and secrets become more prominent in Agent Cooper's investigation into who killed Laura Palmer. As the unbelievable details reveal themselves, he risks everything to learn the truth, including his own soul.

seasons.name: The Return
seasons.overview: Twenty-five years later, the story continues...

tagline: A town where everyone knows everyone and nothing is what it seems.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: The small northwest town of Twin Peaks, Washington is shaken up  when the body of the Homecoming Queen, Laura Palmer, is discovered  washed up on a riverbank, wrapped in plastic.

episodes.name: Traces to Nowhere
episodes.overview: Agent Dale Cooper and Sheriff Harry Truman discover more about the troubled secret life of the murdered Laura Palmer.

episodes.name: Zen, or the Skill to Catch a Killer
episodes.overview: Agent Cooper demonstrates an unusual deductive technique for the Twin Peaks Sheriff's Department.

episodes.name: Rest In Pain
episodes.overview: The people of Twin Peaks gather together to attend the funeral of Laura Palmer.

episodes.name: The One-Armed Man
episodes.overview: Cooper and Truman try to find The One-Armed Man.

guest_stars.character: FBI Regional Bureau Chief Gordon Cole  (voice)
guest_stars.name: David Lynch

episodes.name: Cooper's Dreams
episodes.overview: Cooper and Truman discover a crime scene in the woods.

episodes.name: Realization Time
episodes.overview: Dr. Jacoby gets a phone call from Laura Palmer.

episodes.name: The Last Evening
episodes.overview: The investigation of Laura Palmer's murder reaches a terrifying conclusion.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: It turns out Twin Peaks is not like other towns, and soon FBI Agent Cooper becomes enmeshed with its quirky and mysterious residents.

episodes.name: May the Giant Be with You
episodes.overview: In the aftermath of the incident at the Great Northern Hotel, the investigation into Laura Palmer's death continues, and information is provided from an unexpected source.

episodes.name: Coma
episodes.overview: Cooper receives some unsettling news, while Audrey continues to work undercover as a hostess at One Eyed Jacks in Canada.

episodes.name: The Man Behind the Glass
episodes.overview: Donna meets with Harold Smith, a recluse who may be the key to solving Laura's murder.

episodes.name: Laura's Secret Diary
episodes.overview: Ben Horne asks Cooper for help in rescuing Audrey, and Donna uncovers a significant piece of evidence at Harold Smith's home.

episodes.name: The Orchid's Curse
episodes.overview: Donna, after discovering that Harold has Laura's secret diary, hatches a risky plan with Maddy to steal it from his home.

episodes.name: Demons
episodes.overview: Cooper and Truman cross over into Canada to rescue Audrey, but not all goes according to plan.

episodes.name: Lonely Souls
episodes.overview: Maddy prepares to leave Twin Peaks, Pete uncovers the truth behind Tojamura's intentions, and Cooper receives a devastating message.

episodes.name: Drive with a Dead Girl
episodes.overview: Ben receives an unwelcome surprise, Norma's mother arrives in Twin Peaks with a new husband, and Bob covers his tracks.

episodes.name: Arbitrary Law
episodes.overview: Cooper attempts to locate Laura's killer after the discovery of another victim.

episodes.name: Dispute Between Brothers
episodes.overview: Blaming Cooper for the death of his brother, Jean Renault plots his revenge as the eccentric FBI agent prepares to leave Twin Peaks.

episodes.name: Masked Ball
episodes.overview: With Major Briggs missing, Cooper and Truman look for answers.

episodes.name: The Black Widow
episodes.overview: The investigation into the disappearance of Major Briggs continues, while Bobby tails Hank Jennings at the request of a mentally unstable Ben Horne.

episodes.name: Checkmate
episodes.overview: Major Briggs has no memory of the place he was taken, but now has an odd tattoo on his neck. Andy and Dick break into Little Nicky's files. Mike and Nadine begin an affair. Evelyn asks James to kill her husband.

episodes.name: Double Play
episodes.overview: The rivalry between Cooper and Earle is revealed.

episodes.name: Slaves and Masters
episodes.overview: Agent Cooper finds out who shot him and gets help with his deadly chess game against Windom Earle.

episodes.name: The Condemned Woman
episodes.overview: Ed proposes to Norma; James and Donna say good-bye; and Audrey meets her fated one.

episodes.name: Wounds and Scars
episodes.overview: Cooper is attracted to a beautiful, reclusive woman as Truman grieves over Josie's death.

episodes.name: On the Wings of Love
episodes.overview: Cooper takes the sheriff's department on a midnight spelunking adventure, and Truman finds himself in the deadly embrace of a naked woman.

episodes.name: Variations and Revelations
episodes.overview: While Cooper and Truman try to unlock the secret of Owl Cave, the Miss Twin Peaks contest draws hot competition.

episodes.name: The Path to the Black Lodge
episodes.overview: While romance blooms for Cooper and Annie, Donna finds a scrapbook that's full of surprises.

episodes.name: Miss Twin Peaks
episodes.overview: Cooper and the officers prepare for Windom Earle to make his move at the Miss Twin Peaks contest.

episodes.name: Beyond Life and Death
episodes.overview: Cooper must overcome his deepest fears as he enters the Black Lodge to save Annie from Windom Earle.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: The town's dark side and secrets become more prominent in Agent Cooper's investigation into who killed Laura Palmer. As the unbelievable details reveal themselves, he risks everything to learn the truth, including his own soul.

episodes.name: Part 1
episodes.overview: A man observes a mysterious glass box, South Dakota Police discover a hideous crime and Hawk receives a cryptic message about Special Agent Dale Cooper.

episodes.name: Part 2
episodes.overview: Hawk searches for something in the woods while Cooper learns that his fate in the Black Lodge may not be sealed after all.

episodes.name: Part 3
episodes.overview: Cooper calls for help. Agents Gordon Cole, Albert Rosenfield and Tammy Preston investigate the glass box murders.

episodes.name: Part 4
episodes.overview: Coop assumes the life of Dougie Jones, as Gordon and Agents Rosenfield and Preston investigate the situation surrounding Coop's doppelganger.

episodes.name: Part 5
episodes.overview: Coop is still trapped as Dougie, going through the motions, as his doppelganger schemes in jail. Meanwhile, new information on Major Garland Briggs turns up.

episodes.name: Part 6
episodes.overview: Gordon Cole instructs Albert to meet with an old contact. Hawk makes a discovery involving 'the missing piece' that will help him find Coop. Janey-E fixes Dougie's gambling debt, while Coop is still struggling to put what he knows about his past and the Black Lodge into words. Tragedy strikes after a drug deal takes place.

episodes.name: Part 7
episodes.overview: Cooper and Janey-E are in for a violent surprise at the Lucky 7 office. Meanwhile, Gordon and Albert try enlisting Diane to figure out the mystery of the man they believe to be Cooper in jail.

episodes.name: Part 8
episodes.overview: Coop's doppelganger faces a life or death situation. In 1945, a bomb is dropped and modern man's evil is epitomized.

episodes.name: Part 9
episodes.overview: More about Dougie Jones comes to light after an attempt on his life. Meanwhile, Gordon Cole discovers connections to Cooper concerning a Blue Rose case and Major Garland Briggs.

episodes.name: Part 10
episodes.overview: The Mitchum brothers find out more about Dougie Jones. In Twin Peaks, Richard Horne's committing horrible acts, and Hawk gets more clues from the Log Lady.

episodes.name: Part 11
episodes.overview: The set-up involving the Mitchum brothers and Dougie reaches its climax while even stranger things start to happen to both the FBI team and the Twin Peaks Sheriff's Department.

episodes.name: Part 12
episodes.overview: An old FBI case gets new recruits after many years while well-known residents of Twin Peaks face problems.

episodes.name: Part 13
episodes.overview: Dougie comes home bearing gifts while Anthony is sent on a risky mission, Evil Cooper wants revenge.

episodes.name: Part 14
episodes.overview: Gordon remembers an important moment from his past. Andy, Bobby, Hawk and Truman go to the forest. James hears a story about a glove on his birthday. An unknown facet of Sarah is revealed.

episodes.name: Part 15
episodes.overview: Big Ed and Norma have a relationship breakthrough. Evil Cooper tries to reconnect with an old friend, while Dougie Jones reaches an electrifying discovery.

episodes.name: Part 16
episodes.overview: Dougie's loved ones care for him in the hospital, and Mr. C heads towards the coordinates. Meanwhile, Diane makes a confession to the FBI.

episodes.name: Part 17
episodes.overview: Cooper arrives in Twin Peaks.

episodes.name: Part 18
episodes.overview: Cooper and Diane drive 430 miles. Cooper attempts to help a troubled woman he believes to be Laura Palmer.

3.name: The Return
3.overview: Twenty-five years later, the story continues...
